# Migration files are checksummed by sqlx (tauri-plugin-sql): the EXACT bytes
# at build time are recorded in every installed database, and any later change
# — including a silent CRLF/LF flip by git — makes the app refuse to open
# existing databases ("migration was modified"). Pin the endings forever:
#
#  * 0001–0005 were first applied with CRLF endings  → force CRLF everywhere
#  * 0006 was first applied with LF endings          → keep repo bytes (LF)
#  * future migrations inherit the *.sql rule        → CRLF, deterministic
#
# NEVER edit an applied migration file; add a new numbered migration instead.
apps/desktop/src-tauri/migrations/*.sql text eol=crlf
apps/desktop/src-tauri/migrations/0006_sync_tracking.sql -text
